<paragraph id="D716830F061B237C1BEF1E26FB0DC166" blockId="1.[174,1232,550,716]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">
<keyLead id="6C58203A061B237C1BEF1E26FB0DC166" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">
1. Pronotum and hemelytra with distinct black marks. Cuneus orange, hair of hind tibiae almost as long as the spines, 2nd antennal segment about 2 times as long as width of head. ...................................... 
<taxonomicName id="10A9F88C061B237C1FC31E44FB0DC166" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1877" box="[1154,1230,580,601]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Brachycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steini">
<emphasis id="E5DD5F1D061B237C1FC31E44FB0DC166" box="[1154,1230,580,601]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">B. steini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D716830F061B237C1BEF1E60FB0DC149" blockId="1.[174,1232,550,716]" box="[174,1230,608,630]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">
<keyLead id="6C58203A061B237C1BEF1E60FB0DC149" box="[174,1230,608,630]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">— Pronotum and hemelytra without distinct black marks. [Other characters variable]. .............................. 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="6C5D9BAA061B237C1BEF1E7DFB0DC1F3" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">
<paragraph id="D716830F061B237C1BEF1E7DFB0DC190" blockId="1.[174,1232,550,716]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">
<keyLead id="6C58203A061B237C1BEF1E7DFB0DC190" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">
2. Pronotum bright, with 1 or 3 small dark longitudinal stripes. Corium pale, each with only a narrow dark longitudinal stripes on clavus and on the radial artery. ................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="10A9F88C061B237C1F291E9AFB0DC190" authorityName="Jakovlev" authorityYear="1884" box="[1128,1230,666,687]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Brachycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineellus">
<emphasis id="E5DD5F1D061B237C1F291E9AFB0DC190" box="[1128,1230,666,687]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">B. lineellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D716830F061B237C1BEF1EB6FB0DC1F3" blockId="1.[174,1232,550,716]" box="[174,1230,694,716]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">
<keyLead id="6C58203A061B237C1BEF1EB6FB0DC1F3" box="[174,1230,694,716]" pageId="1" pageNumber="106">
— Pronotum bright, without dark longitudinal stripes. Corium not as above. ........................... 
